snippet.textDisplay:
No special treatment. When in Rome, you follow Roman (empire) rules. When in Australia, you follow Australian rules. The entry requirements were made very clear. AND IT IS AN INHERENT POWER AND RIGHT OF A SOVEREIGN STATE TO ENFORCE ITS BORDER LAWS. IT IS OUR BORDER. Who does he think he is? He’s a tennis player. He’s not above the law. Sportsmanship is all about rules, no foul play. Should have known better than* expecting special treatment. If you don’t intend to follow Australian rules, don’t come and be subject to it. 

Not his first time visiting Australia, let alone during a pandemic. He has been given special treatment as is - an ordinary person would have been detained and then deported the next day out of the country. 

Anyone entering Australia and lying on their application or not meeting an entry requirement gets deported and banned entry for three years. And Australia has every right to exercise its discretion in matters relating to entry, stay, and deportation. Period.
